2. Prosopodonta costata. (Tab. 11. fig. 7.)

Oblongo-elongata, subtus nigra, nitida3 thorace fulvo-picem supra piceo-fulva, antennis nigris 3 thorace quam longo vix latiori, lateribus leviter rotundatis, basi fere rectis, disco convexo, laevi, basi et ad latera punctat03 elytris oblongis, convexis, fortiter punctato-ariam, striis biseriatim dispoffitis, interspatiis secundo et quarto metatis, costa exteriori [nec non limbo laterali] sordide fulvis.

Hah. PANAMA, Volcan de Chiriqui 2000 to 3000 feet (Ohampion).

Head smooth and shining3 face armed between the antennae with an acute tooth. Antennae rather longer than the head and thoraX, distinctly thickened towards the apert, the joints cylindrical. Thorax rather broader than long: sides obtusely rounded, obsoletely angulate immediately behind and again just before the middle, straight and slightly diverging at the base, converging from the middle to the apert, apical angle not produced, obtuse; upper surface convert, smooth and shining, impressed on the sides and hinder disc with large deep punctures. Elytra oblong, subparallel, regularly rounded at the apex3 strongly punctate-striate, the striae (nine at the extreme base and eight on the rest of the surface) arranged in double rows; alternate interspaces slightly elevated, the second and fourth from the suture more strongly thickened, costate.

The present insect differs entirely in the coloration of its thorax from any hitherto described species of the genus.
